items.title: Syria to join US-led coalition to defeat IS group after Trump meeting
items.description: Ahmed al-Sharaa, once branded a terrorist by the US, became the first Syrian leader to visit the White House.

items.title: Gaddafi's youngest son released after 10 years in Lebanese detention
items.description: The Lebanese authorities seized Mr Gaddafi, now 49, in 2015 and held him without trial.

items.title: Ros Atkins on... the BBC resignations
items.description: The BBC's Analysis Editor Ros Atkins looks at the resignations of BBC bosses - and how this crisis didn't come out of nowhere.

items.title: Canada loses its measles-free status, with US on track to follow
items.description: The country hasn't been able to curb an outbreak of more than 5,000 cases over the last year, while US cases are at a 33-year high.

items.title: At least eight killed after car explodes near Delhi's Red Fort
items.description: Twenty more were injured in the blast, the cause of which is still unknown, authorities say.
